Stay tuned about 20 minutes, and
you will see not very natural

00:53:36.630 --> 00:53:38.350
at all.

00:53:38.350 --> 00:53:41.320
As soon as you get to humans,
all this social biology

00:53:41.320 --> 00:53:43.840
stuff with kin selection
is interesting, but as

00:53:43.840 --> 00:53:47.180
soon as you get to humans you
get to something vastly more

00:53:47.180 --> 00:53:48.970
interesting and important.

00:53:48.970 --> 00:53:52.380
Back to our recognizing
relatives realm--

00:53:52.380 --> 00:53:56.680
the business of how we interact
not with our relatives,

00:53:56.680 --> 00:54:00.430
but with people who we
feel as close to as if they

00:54:00.430 --> 00:54:03.900
are relatives-- pseudo kinship.

00:54:03.900 --> 00:54:06.890
And what you see in
culture after culture

00:54:06.890 --> 00:54:11.990
is brilliant manipulative skills
on the part of powers that

00:54:11.990 --> 00:54:16.080
be to make some non-relatives
feel more related to each other

00:54:16.080 --> 00:54:17.780
than they actually are.

00:54:17.780 --> 00:54:19.100
What's this about?

00:54:19.100 --> 00:54:21.860
This is military indoctrination.

00:54:21.860 --> 00:54:24.160
The whole point, or
one of the main points,

00:54:24.160 --> 00:54:27.000
of military training
early on is to get

00:54:27.000 --> 00:54:30.400
people to become a
band of brothers,

00:54:30.400 --> 00:54:33.060
a band of pseudo
kinshipped relatives,

00:54:33.060 --> 00:54:36.360
to increase the
cooperativity later on,

00:54:36.360 --> 00:54:37.860
to increase the
odds that you are

00:54:37.860 --> 00:54:40.400
willing to give up your life
for the person next to you.

00:54:40.400 --> 00:54:43.060
Culture after culture
is great at doing this.

00:54:43.060 --> 00:54:46.540
Warrior cultures-- for example,
the Maasai in East Africa,

00:54:46.540 --> 00:54:48.840
they have a warrior
stage when you're 15,

00:54:48.840 --> 00:54:51.010
you go become a
warrior, roughly 15.

00:54:51.010 --> 00:54:52.840
And you stay that
way for a decade.

00:54:52.840 --> 00:54:54.170
And you protect the cows.

00:54:54.170 --> 00:54:55.300
And you raid the neighbors.

00:54:55.300 --> 00:54:57.680
And once you're 25,
you become an elder

00:54:57.680 --> 00:55:00.520
and get married then
to a 13-year-old.

00:55:00.520 --> 00:55:05.260
But what you've got there is
the entire structure of warrior

00:55:05.260 --> 00:55:07.880
life is built around
pseudo kinship.

00:55:07.880 --> 00:55:10.860
They live separately
from everybody else.

00:55:10.860 --> 00:55:13.870
They use kinship
terms for each other.

00:55:13.870 --> 00:55:16.440
For the rest of their
lives, their wife

00:55:16.440 --> 00:55:19.100
will refer to somebody
from their warrior class

00:55:19.100 --> 00:55:21.390
as her brother-in-law.

00:55:21.390 --> 00:55:24.450
Warriors are not allowed
to eat their own food.

00:55:24.450 --> 00:55:27.640
They can only share their
food with another warrior,

00:55:27.640 --> 00:55:31.440
all built around
generating pseudo kinship.

00:55:31.440 --> 00:55:34.850
Other version, that other
more industrialized version,

00:55:34.850 --> 00:55:37.310
the Israeli Military,
for example,

00:55:37.310 --> 00:55:40.680
allows kids when they are
signing up after high school

00:55:40.680 --> 00:55:44.740
to join particular units as
a group, a group of friends

00:55:44.740 --> 00:55:47.970
from their high school,
increasing the pseudo kinship

00:55:47.970 --> 00:55:49.790
element there.

00:55:49.790 --> 00:55:54.390
More of that-- something that
was absolutely unprecedented

00:55:54.390 --> 00:55:58.100
when you look at the difference
between kinship and pseudo

00:55:58.100 --> 00:55:58.870
kinship.

00:55:58.870 --> 00:56:03.630
World War II, United States
hugely heterogeneous country,

00:56:03.630 --> 00:56:06.850
obviously, blah, blah,
melting pot, all of that.

00:56:06.850 --> 00:56:10.710
And World War II was sort
of the peak of that picture.

00:56:10.710 --> 00:56:13.770
And what you got in
many, many fighting units

00:56:13.770 --> 00:56:16.100
was something straight
out of central casting

00:56:16.100 --> 00:56:17.820
in these inspirational movies.

00:56:17.820 --> 00:56:23.240
There's McCarthy from Boston,
and Sapiola from Philadelphia,

00:56:23.240 --> 00:56:26.700
and Kewalski from Chicago,
and then the Southern guy,

00:56:26.700 --> 00:56:28.540
and the Jewish guy
from who knows where.

00:56:28.540 --> 00:56:29.940
And they're all together.

00:56:29.940 --> 00:56:33.030
And they're a fighting
unit of American unity,

00:56:33.030 --> 00:56:33.930
and all of that.

00:56:33.930 --> 00:56:35.590
And what does that produce?

00:56:35.590 --> 00:56:39.040
Something that was virtually
unprecedented in warfare.

00:56:39.040 --> 00:56:41.990
If you were an American
soldier in World War II

00:56:41.990 --> 00:56:46.360
and you were of German-American
or German ancestry,

00:56:46.360 --> 00:56:48.740
you would, on the
average, almost certainly

00:56:48.740 --> 00:56:52.160
share more genes in common
with the people you were trying

00:56:52.160 --> 00:56:54.770
to kill than the people
you were willing to give up

00:56:54.770 --> 00:56:58.390
your life for, as you had
classically heterogeneous

00:56:58.390 --> 00:57:02.880
troops on the American side--
completely unprecedented,

00:57:02.880 --> 00:57:06.040
so this business
of pseudo kinship.

00:57:06.040 --> 00:57:08.080
Historically, Vietnam
was apparently

00:57:08.080 --> 00:57:12.570
a major failure of military
pseudo kinship mechanisms,

00:57:12.570 --> 00:57:15.490
in that something
unprecedented was done there,

00:57:15.490 --> 00:57:20.050
which was people were not
kept in stable fighting units.

00:57:20.050 --> 00:57:22.940
Instead, people were constantly
shuttling in and out.

00:57:22.940 --> 00:57:25.640
And you would get these nutty
circumstances, apparently,

00:57:25.640 --> 00:57:27.980
where you'd be there in the
middle of the firefight.

00:57:27.980 --> 00:57:31.220
And the person over here is some
kid who showed up this morning.

00:57:31.220 --> 00:57:33.070
And the guy here,
if he survives this,

00:57:33.070 --> 00:57:35.840
he's shipping out home
to Hawaii tonight.

00:57:35.840 --> 00:57:37.940
And who feels like a brother?

00:57:37.940 --> 00:57:38.890
No one.

00:57:38.890 --> 00:57:43.490
Vietnam had an unmatched degree
of breaking of unity of troops.

00:57:43.490 --> 00:57:44.960
Why was that done in Vietnam?

00:57:44.960 --> 00:57:46.600
Something that kept happening.

00:57:46.600 --> 00:57:49.930
As soon as they allowed
units to remain more stable,

00:57:49.930 --> 00:57:52.520
the rates at which soldiers
were shooting their officers

00:57:52.520 --> 00:57:54.910
would go way up.

00:57:54.910 --> 00:57:58.990
So another, perhaps,
version of cooperation.

00:57:58.990 --> 00:58:01.500
Hand-in-hand with
the pseudo kinship

00:58:01.500 --> 00:58:05.490
is, of course, the flip
side, pseudo speciation,

00:58:05.490 --> 00:58:08.650
the mechanisms, the
psychological, the propagandist

00:58:08.650 --> 00:58:12.950
mechanisms that are available
to make them seem as

00:58:12.950 --> 00:58:15.170
different from you as possible.

00:58:15.170 --> 00:58:17.540
Not just different
sorts of people,

00:58:17.540 --> 00:58:21.800
but pseudo speciation-- they
are so different they hardly

00:58:21.800 --> 00:58:23.890
even count as humans.

00:58:23.890 --> 00:58:26.300
It doesn't count as
much when you kill them.

00:58:26.300 --> 00:58:30.590
And endless realms of that
World War II propaganda

00:58:30.590 --> 00:58:33.450
in the United
States about various

00:58:33.450 --> 00:58:35.160
ethnicities that
we were fighting

00:58:35.160 --> 00:58:39.340
against pseudo speciating,
various genocides, the Rwandan

00:58:39.340 --> 00:58:39.840
one.

00:58:39.840 --> 00:58:44.450
The sort of call to arms there
was kill the cockroaches,

00:58:44.450 --> 00:58:47.700
kill the cockroaches, the
Hutu tribes killing the Tutsis

00:58:47.700 --> 00:58:48.270
there.

00:58:48.270 --> 00:58:50.970
And this was pseudo speciation.

00:58:50.970 --> 00:58:53.910
Let me give you an
amazing example which

00:58:53.910 --> 00:58:58.510
occurred in this country not
all that long ago around 1990.

00:58:58.510 --> 00:59:01.280
An astonishing piece
of pseudo speciation

00:59:01.280 --> 00:59:06.540
that happened in this
country-- 1990, first Gulf War.

00:59:06.540 --> 00:59:11.800
Kuwait was drilling oil from
underneath the Iraq's land.

00:59:11.800 --> 00:59:13.780
Iraq got pissed
off, invaded them.

00:59:13.780 --> 00:59:15.750
And, suddenly, we had
the first Gulf War.

00:59:15.750 --> 00:59:19.910
The United States goes in
there to drive the Iraqis out

00:59:19.910 --> 00:59:20.620
of Kuwait.

00:59:20.620 --> 00:59:22.280
And ultimately has
to make the decision

00:59:22.280 --> 00:59:25.300
of whether to follow them
into Iraq and overthrow

00:59:25.300 --> 00:59:26.350
Saddam Hussein.

00:59:26.350 --> 00:59:27.440
And that wasn't done.

00:59:27.440 --> 00:59:29.360
But so this war going on.

00:59:29.360 --> 00:59:31.950
Very early on, it
was absolutely clear

00:59:31.950 --> 00:59:37.250
where it was heading, which was
that the diplomacy was failing.

00:59:37.250 --> 00:59:38.830
And the United
States was beginning

00:59:38.830 --> 00:59:41.660
to pull together a coalition
of various countries

00:59:41.660 --> 00:59:44.270
that would be a unified
force fighting against Iraq.

00:59:44.270 --> 00:59:47.560
But it had not yet been
authorized by US Congress

00:59:47.560 --> 00:59:49.620
as an act of war.

00:59:49.620 --> 00:59:53.290
Suddenly, into
this came a woman,

00:59:53.290 --> 00:59:56.220
a refugee from Kuwait City.

00:59:56.220 --> 00:59:59.650
Refugee, she was a nurse who
worked in a hospital there.

00:59:59.650 --> 01:00:01.840
She had managed to
get out of Kuwait

01:00:01.840 --> 01:00:03.770
after the Iraqis had invaded.

01:00:03.770 --> 01:00:06.810
And she came and
testified in Congress

01:00:06.810 --> 01:00:10.120
about an appalling thing
that she had witnessed,

01:00:10.120 --> 01:00:13.580
which was when the Iraqis
came in and took over

01:00:13.580 --> 01:00:17.790
their hospital, not only did
they steal all the supplies.

01:00:17.790 --> 01:00:21.470
They took the newborn
infants out of the incubators

01:00:21.470 --> 01:00:24.830
and left them out to die, and
shipped the incubators back

01:00:24.830 --> 01:00:26.650
to Iraq.

01:00:26.650 --> 01:00:29.740
Everyone was
flabbergasted by this.

01:00:29.740 --> 01:00:33.490
This was every newspaper
in the country, everybody

01:00:33.490 --> 01:00:34.760
learned about this.

01:00:34.760 --> 01:00:39.440
Everybody suddenly learned,
my God, they leave babies out

01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:40.320
to die.

01:00:40.320 --> 01:00:43.160
These people hardly
count as human.

01:00:43.160 --> 01:00:46.740
And, critically, that war
was authorized by Congress

01:00:46.740 --> 01:00:49.060
by just a couple of
votes of senators.

01:00:49.060 --> 01:00:50.920
And at least a
half dozen of them

01:00:50.920 --> 01:00:54.320
cited this incident in helping
them decide and this was

01:00:54.320 --> 01:00:56.040
something that had to be done.

01:00:56.040 --> 01:00:59.810
This was a deciding factor
in us going to that war.

01:00:59.810 --> 01:01:04.060
And the remarkable thing
is, it never happened.

01:01:04.060 --> 01:01:07.340
The nurse was not a
nurse from Kuwait City.

01:01:07.340 --> 01:01:11.030
She was the niece of
the Kuwaiti ambassador

01:01:11.030 --> 01:01:12.810
to the United States.

01:01:12.810 --> 01:01:15.550
She had been trained
by a public relations

01:01:15.550 --> 01:01:18.050
firm paid for by
the US government

01:01:18.050 --> 01:01:19.700
to make up this story.

01:01:19.700 --> 01:01:23.070
And she sat in our
Congress on live TV

01:01:23.070 --> 01:01:26.360
in front of the entire
country, lied like crazy.

01:01:26.360 --> 01:01:30.980
And we went into that war
with a 92% approval rate-- one

01:01:30.980 --> 01:01:33.930
gigantic piece of
pseudo speciation.

01:01:33.930 --> 01:01:37.170
My God, they leave
babies out to die.

01:01:37.170 --> 01:01:39.490
It will hardly
count killing them.

01:01:39.490 --> 01:01:41.490
They're hardly even human.

01:01:41.490 --> 01:01:44.360
And the coverage of when it
was revealed what was actually

01:01:44.360 --> 01:01:47.930
going on with this person
didn't come anywhere close

01:01:47.930 --> 01:01:51.510
to front page in any newspaper
in the country, buried down

01:01:51.510 --> 01:01:52.230
in there.

01:01:52.230 --> 01:01:55.430
Virtually the entire country
came out of that incident

01:01:55.430 --> 01:01:58.840
having learned how
inhumane, those people

01:01:58.840 --> 01:02:01.010
hardly count as human.

