with each other.

01:04:02.660 --> 01:04:05.350
This is a ritual in
all sorts of societies

01:04:05.350 --> 01:04:07.940
where you generate
pseudo kinship

01:04:07.940 --> 01:04:10.180
as a means of generating peace.

01:04:10.180 --> 01:04:14.200
One example, traditional Bedouin
society, here's what happens.

01:04:14.200 --> 01:04:16.770
You have two groups who have
been having tensions, who've

01:04:16.770 --> 01:04:19.440
been fighting, who have been
having some clan warfare,

01:04:19.440 --> 01:04:20.260
whatever.

01:04:20.260 --> 01:04:22.550
And they have now
figured out a way

01:04:22.550 --> 01:04:25.440
to have a treaty to stop
fighting with each other.

01:04:25.440 --> 01:04:28.170
Here is the ritual
that is done, which

01:04:28.170 --> 01:04:31.390
is a bunch of the old guys
from each of the groups come.

01:04:31.390 --> 01:04:32.490
And they sit down.

01:04:32.490 --> 01:04:36.020
And they start exploring
each other's genealogies.

01:04:36.020 --> 01:04:37.572
Who is your great grandparents?

01:04:37.572 --> 01:04:40.030
Who is your great, great, great,
going through all of that.

01:04:40.030 --> 01:04:42.700
And at some point, one
of them has the job

01:04:42.700 --> 01:04:46.460
of making up an imaginary
relationship between the two

01:04:46.460 --> 01:04:47.740
groups.

01:04:47.740 --> 01:04:49.510
Chuck, are you kidding?

01:04:49.510 --> 01:04:52.400
I had a great, great
grandfather named Chuck also.

01:04:52.400 --> 01:04:54.020
We're relatives.

01:04:54.020 --> 01:04:57.480
A ritual absolutely transparent
that people go through

01:04:57.480 --> 01:05:02.520
there to generate a supposed
rationale for relatedness,

01:05:02.520 --> 01:05:05.850
a big ceremony of
pseudo kinship.

01:05:05.850 --> 01:05:09.700
Another one is seen in some
aboriginal groups in Australia.

01:05:09.700 --> 01:05:12.520
Apparently, this is a
motif that pops up often

01:05:12.520 --> 01:05:14.780
in aboriginal rock art.

01:05:14.780 --> 01:05:19.000
And, apparently, it's a symbolic
version of this phenomenon.

01:05:19.000 --> 01:05:21.230
OK, you've got
somebody wandering

01:05:21.230 --> 01:05:23.750
through the great
back of beyond there.

01:05:23.750 --> 01:05:27.130
And there are very
few sources of water.

01:05:27.130 --> 01:05:28.960
There's a water hole up ahead.

01:05:28.960 --> 01:05:31.390
You've just walked 10
miles to come to it.

01:05:31.390 --> 01:05:34.080
And you suddenly
notice a stranger

01:05:34.080 --> 01:05:37.920
coming towards the water hole
from the opposite direction.

01:05:37.920 --> 01:05:42.300
And this is a water hole that
is essential for you to survive.

01:05:42.300 --> 01:05:44.570
You are not going to be able
to walk far enough to get

01:05:44.570 --> 01:05:46.000
to the next water hole.

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:48.550
Maybe what you should
do, just in case

01:05:48.550 --> 01:05:50.460
this person winds
up being aggressive,

01:05:50.460 --> 01:05:53.990
is you should attack him
first-- a virtual guarantee

01:05:53.990 --> 01:05:55.060
of aggression.

01:05:55.060 --> 01:05:57.950
Here's a ritual that has
been worked out instead

01:05:57.950 --> 01:05:59.660
that bypasses it.

01:05:59.660 --> 01:06:02.660
The two individuals sit
down around the waterhole.

01:06:02.660 --> 01:06:06.140
And each starts giving
their genealogy.

01:06:06.140 --> 01:06:08.530
I am the son of, who's the
son of, who's the son of.

01:06:08.530 --> 01:06:10.560
Into the next bar
mitzvah, whatever.

01:06:10.560 --> 01:06:12.460
Oh, we're relatives.

01:06:12.460 --> 01:06:14.280
Let's share some water.

01:06:14.280 --> 01:06:15.900
They don't fall for
it for a second.

01:06:15.900 --> 01:06:19.250
But it is a totally artificial
mechanism of pseudo kinship

01:06:19.250 --> 01:06:21.660
to make it possible
for two strangers

01:06:21.660 --> 01:06:25.010
to share this absolutely
essential for life resource,

01:06:25.010 --> 01:06:27.530
and not try to kill each other.

01:06:27.530 --> 01:06:29.860
Same sort of thing,
pseudo kinship

01:06:29.860 --> 01:06:33.830
in all sorts of historical
examples, of revolutions.

